In this simulation will be using Ubuntu Server 24.04 LTS

## perfdhcp is a tool to used to test DHCP server performance (part of ISC DHCP / Kea).
Procedure
1. Install perfdhcp DHCP testing tool.
$sudo apt install kea-admin

2. Simulate perfdhcp to server
# perfdhcp -4 -R 10 -p 120 -l ens160      

Details
-4 → Use IPv4 (instead of IPv6).
-R 10 → Send packets at a rate of 10 requests per second.
-p 120 → Use 120 parallel clients/sessions (simulated DHCP clients).
-l ens160 → Bind to the network interface named ens160

In plain terms
You’re simulating 120 DHCP clients on interface ens160, generating traffic at 10 requests per second, to measure how a DHCP server responds under load.

Typical use case
This is commonly used to:
-Stress-test a DHCP server (like Kea DHCP or ISC DHCP)
-Measure lease allocation performance
-Diagnose bottlenecks in network provisioning
